LuaScript:
function onload()
    vDebug = true
    setupObjects = {
        bottleBag = "bottleBag",
        objectiveBoard = "objectiveBoard",
        wheel = "wheel",
        palettes = "palettes",
        xTokens = "xTokens",
        xxTokens = "xxTokens",
        tiles = "tiles",
        startingTiles = "startingTiles",
        tileBag = "tileBag",
        setupButton = "setupButton"
        --bottlecardBlue = "bottlecardBlue",
        --bottlecardRed = "bottlecardRed",
        --bottlecardYellow = "bottlecardYellow",
        --bottlecardPurple = "bottlecardPurple",
    }
    playerCount = 2
    prefix = "[bffbf2][SAGRADA][-]"
    allObjects = getAllObjects()
    for o, object in ipairs(allObjects) do
        if #object.getTags() >= 1 then
            for t, tag in ipairs(object.getTags()) do
                if setupObjects[tag] ~= nil then
                    setupObjects[tag] = object
                end
            end
        end
    end
    --for t = 1, #setupObjects.tiles.getObjects(), 1 do
    --    local takenTile = setupObjects.tiles.takeObject()
    --    setupObjects.tileBag.putObject(takenTile)
    --end
    createPaletteSnaps()
    createObjectiveSnaps()
    setupButtons()
end

function setupButtons()
    local setupButtonParameters = {
        click_function = "setPlayerCountTwo",
        function_owner = Global,
        label          = "2P",
        position       = {2.5,0,0},
        rotation       = {0,180,0},
        width          = 1000,
        height         = 1000,
        font_size      = 400,
        color          = {0.2,0.2,0.2},
        font_color     = {0.9,0.9,0.9},
        scale          = {1,1,1},
        tooltip = "Setup game for 2 players"
    }
    setupObjects.setupButton.createButton(setupButtonParameters)
    setupButtonParameters.label = "3P"
    setupButtonParameters.click_function = "setPlayerCountThree"
    setupButtonParameters.tooltip = "Setup game for 3 players"
    setupButtonParameters.position = {0,0,0}
    setupObjects.setupButton.createButton(setupButtonParameters)
    setupButtonParameters.label = "4P"
    setupButtonParameters.click_function = "setPlayerCountFour"
    setupButtonParameters.tooltip = "Setup game for 4 players"
    setupButtonParameters.position = {-2.5,0,0}
    setupObjects.setupButton.createButton(setupButtonParameters)
end

function setPlayerCountTwo() playerCount = 2 setupGame() end
function setPlayerCountThree() playerCount = 3 setupGame() end
function setPlayerCountFour() playerCount = 4 setupGame() end

function setupGame()
    setupObjects.setupButton.clearButtons()
    Wait.time(function() setupXXCards() end, 0.4, 1)
    Wait.time(function() setupXCards() end, 0.8, 1)
    Wait.time(function() setupPalettes() end, 1.2, 1)
    Wait.time(function() setupBottles() end, 1.6, 1)
    Wait.time(function() setupStartingTiles() end, 2, 1)
    Wait.time(function() setupWheelTiles() end, 2.4, 1)
    Wait.time(function() setupObjectives() end, 2.4, 1)
end

function createPaletteSnaps()
    local bottleCards = {}
    for o, object in ipairs(allObjects) do
        if object.hasTag("bottleCard") then
            table.insert(bottleCards, object)
        end
    end
    for c, card in ipairs(bottleCards) do
        card.setSnapPoints({})
        local snapStartPosition = Vector(-1, 1, -1.5)
        local snapOffsetX = 0.5
        local snapOffsetZ = 0.6
        local snaps = {}
        for z = 1, 4, 1 do
            for x = 1, 3, 1 do
                local snapPosition = Vector(snapStartPosition.x + (snapOffsetX * x), 0, snapStartPosition.z + (snapOffsetZ * z))
                local newSnap = {position=snapPosition, rotation={0,0,0}, rotation_snap=true}
                table.insert(snaps, newSnap)
            end
        end
        card.setSnapPoints(snaps)
    end
end

function createObjectiveSnaps()
    setupObjects.objectiveBoard.setSnapPoints({})
    local snapStartPosition = Vector(-1.05, 1, -2.5)
    local snapOffsetX = 0.35
    local snapOffsetZ = 0.35
    local snaps = {}
    for z = 1, 3, 1 do
        for x = 1, 5, 1 do
            local snapPosition = Vector(snapStartPosition.x + (snapOffsetX * x), 0, snapStartPosition.z + (snapOffsetZ * z))
            local newSnap = {position=snapPosition, rotation={0,0,0}, rotation_snap=true}
            table.insert(snaps, newSnap)
        end
    end
    setupObjects.objectiveBoard.setSnapPoints(snaps)
    --setupGame()
end

function setupObjectives()
    --objectivesOdd = {
    --    {value = 1, label="Place 1 white spot on a free square"},
    --    {value = 3, label="Place 1 colored square of your choice"},
    --    {value = 5, label="Remove 1 ink bottle"},
    --    {value = 7, label="Pick 1 tile from the wheel and keep it for a later turn"},
    --    {value = 9, label="Place 1 tile from the wheel and keep it for a later turn"},
    --    {value = 11, label="Draw 1 tile from the bag and play it immediately"}
    --}
    --objectivesEven = {
    --    {value = 2, label="Change the number of an Objective"},
    --    {value = 4, label="Move 1 tile from the edge of your painting"},
    --    {value = 6, label="Move up to 2 ink bottles"},
    --    {value = 8, label="Remove 1 ink bottle"},
    --    {value = 10, label="Move up to 2 ink bottles"},
    --    {value = 12, label="Each opponent draws a token from the X bag"}
    --}
    objectives = {
        {value = 1, label="Place 1 white spot\non a free square"},
        {value = 3, label="Place 1 colored square\nof your choice"},
        {value = 5, label="Remove 1 ink bottle"},
        {value = 7, label="Pick 1 tile from the wheel\nand keep it for a later turn"},
        {value = 9, label="Place 1 tile from the wheel\nand keep it for a later turn"},
        {value = 11, label="Draw 1 tile from the bag\nand play it immediately"},
        {value = 2, label="Change the number\nof an Objective"},
        {value = 4, label="Move 1 tile from the\nedge of your painting"},
        {value = 6, label="Move up to 2 ink bottles"},
        {value = 8, label="Remove 1 ink bottle"},
        {value = 10, label="Move up to 2 ink bottles"},
        {value = 12, label="Each opponent draws\na token from the X bag"},
    }
    local objectiveValues = {}
    local oddRandA = math.random(1,6)
    local oddRandB = math.random(1,6)
    while oddRandB == oddRandA do
        oddRandB = math.random(1,6)
    end
    table.insert(objectiveValues, oddRandA)
    table.insert(objectiveValues, oddRandB)
    local evenRandA = math.random(7,12)
    local evenRandB = math.random(7,12)
    while evenRandB == evenRandA do
        evenRandB = math.random(7,12)
    end
    table.insert(objectiveValues, evenRandA)
    table.insert(objectiveValues, evenRandB)
    table.sort(objectiveValues)
    local buttonPositions = {
        {0.2,0.08,-0.63},
        {0.2,0.08,-0.21},
        {0.2,0.08, 0.23},
        {0.2,0.08, 0.65},
    }
    local buttonScale = 0.2
    for o, objective in ipairs(objectiveValues) do
        local objectiveDisplay = {
            click_function = "none",
            function_owner = Global,
            label          = objectives[o].label,
            position       = buttonPositions[o],
            rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
            width          = 3000,
            height         = 800,
            font_size      = 250,
            color          = {0.2,0.2,0.2},
            font_color     = {0.9,0.9,0.9},
            scale          = {buttonScale,buttonScale,buttonScale}
        }
        setupObjects.objectiveBoard.createButton(objectiveDisplay)
    end
end

function none()
end

function setupBottles()
    local bottleCards = {}
    local bottleSnaps = {}
    for o, object in ipairs(allObjects) do
        if object.hasTag("bottleCard") then
            for s, snap in ipairs(object.getSnapPoints()) do
                local takenBottle = setupObjects.bottleBag.takeObject({position = object.positionToWorld(Vector(snap.position))})
                takenBottle.setColorTint(object.getColorTint())
            end
        end
    end
    local objectiveSnaps = setupObjects.objectiveBoard.getSnapPoints()
    for s, snap in ipairs(objectiveSnaps) do
        local takenBottle = setupObjects.bottleBag.takeObject({position = setupObjects.objectiveBoard.positionToWorld(Vector(snap.position))})
    end
end

function setupXXCards()
    local xTokenPosition = Vector(0.00, 2.21, 2.85)
    local heightOffset = 0
    setupObjects.xTokens.randomize()
    setupObjects.xxTokens.randomize()
    for i = 1, 20, 1 do
        local pos = Vector(xTokenPosition.x, xTokenPosition.y + heightOffset, xTokenPosition.z)
        setupObjects.xxTokens.takeObject({position=pos, rotation={0,180,180}})
        heightOffset = heightOffset + 0.05
    end
end

function setupXCards()
    local xTokenPosition = Vector(0.00, 2.21, 2.85)
    local heightOffset = 1.5
    for i = 1, playerCount do
        for x = 1, 3, 1 do
            local pos = Vector(xTokenPosition.x, xTokenPosition.y + heightOffset, xTokenPosition.z)
            setupObjects.xTokens.takeObject({position=pos, rotation={0,180,180}})
            heightOffset = heightOffset + 0.05
        end
    end
end

function setupPalettes()
    local palettesInitialPosition = setupObjects.palettes.getPosition()
    local paletteParameters = {
        {pos=Vector(-28.00, 2.04, -25.00), rot=Vector(0,180,0)},
        {pos=Vector(0.00, 2.04, -25.00), rot=Vector(0,180,0)},
        {pos=Vector(28.00, 2.04, 25.00), rot=Vector(0,0,0)},
        {pos=Vector(0.00, 2.04, 25.00), rot=Vector(0,0,0)},
    }
    setupObjects.palettes.randomize()
    for p, palette in ipairs(paletteParameters) do
        local takenPalette = setupObjects.palettes.takeObject({position=palette.pos, rotation=palette.rot})
        Wait.time(function() takenPalette.setLock(true) end, 0.5, 1)
    end
end

function setupStartingTiles()
    local startingTileParameters = {
        {pos=Vector(-13.88, 2.01, -13.88), rot=Vector(0,180,0)},
        {pos=Vector(13.88, 2.01, -13.88), rot=Vector(0,180,0)},
        {pos=Vector(12.95, 2.01, 12.95), rot=Vector(0,0,0)},
        {pos=Vector(-14.80, 2.01, 12.95), rot=Vector(0,0,0)},
    }
    setupObjects.startingTiles.randomize()
    for t, tile in ipairs(startingTileParameters) do
        setupObjects.startingTiles.takeObject({position=tile.pos, rotation=tile.rot})
    end
end

function setupWheelTiles()
    local snaps = setupObjects.wheel.getSnapPoints()
    for s, snap in ipairs(snaps) do
        setupObjects.tileBag.takeObject({position=setupObjects.wheel.positionToWorld(snap.position), rotation=Vector(snap.rotation):add(Vector(0,180,0))})
    end
end
function findCast(pos,size,type)
    local hitList = Physics.cast({
        origin       = pos,
        direction    = {0,-0.01,0},
        type         = type,
        size         = size,
        max_distance = 100,
        debug        = vDebug,
    })
    return hitList
end
